content.description: short but interesting climb up along a diagonal crack.  Then a big move to the crack above followed by a big move to the top. Start just to the right of a 6' tree stump.  Work the tricky ledge to the left to get your hands in the diag. crack.
content.protection: toprope.  Lots of trees at the top to tie off to. The trees you need to get anchors equalized are 40 feet off.
content.location: You can top out and walk off.  Head up to the RR overlook.  You can't miss the wall area.  Go to the far right section just shy of being under the nose.  Photo included.

content.description: Climb the far right face of the wall without using the front face or adjoining boulder.  Crux is connecting the bottom to the top.  Very short on good holds in the middle.
content.location: Outlook Wall - section to the far right just before being under the point.

content.description: Up the AT to the Raven Rock outlook.  You can drop topropes over the outlook.  There are a number of large, secure trees within 30-50 feet of the edge.  Sides are well shaded, front gets afternoon sun.  It's very rarely crowded - more hikers than climbers. Some good bouldering and some short but challenging toproping walls.
